had a little sunrise reflection time this morning.  working hard every day to be my best and mostly feeling deeply inspired.  but today woke up imbalanced, frustrated, disappointed with myself.  and after some meditation, some stillness in the sunshine - i realized something.  sometimes the work is just to keep going, to muddle through despite all odds.  other times, it is to totally pull back, protect, be still.  but these days i am learning to trust - in others, the process, and in myself.... i am learning to trust in the beautiful, wild, intense structure i’ve built to hold me.. and to trust that i already own everything i need.               notlose        yurvedalife

text:
@gediroutekishtwar1

kishtwar dc office complex shocker, girl rape inside complex premises
#metoo# campaign fallout : teenage girl file rape complaint against handloom employee

asif iqbal naik
kishtwar october 13: in a shocking incident of misuse of government office in kishtwar district situated within the premises of new dc office complex kishtwar, a teenage girl inspired from #metoo# campaign filed a rape complaint against the employee of handloom department and his friend for blackmailing by recording her porn videos, threatening and abusive behavior towards her.

as per the details available with “early times”, the teenage girl (name withheld) today file a written complaint before station house police officer kishtwar alleging that the accused meet her about two years ago and proposed her to be his friend added that with the passage of time the accused got close intimacy with her and offered her a marriage proposal. 
she said that at first instance she was reluctant to accept the marriage proposal offered to her by the accused but after rethinking over it, she stated that she agreed the said marriage proposal from the accused.

she said that the accused taking the advantage of her innocence took her to a hotel in jammu and committed sexual intercourse on her under the influence of fraud and by cheating her wherein he captured her videos and photographs and continue to blackmail her during all these years till she got the courage and inspiration from #metoo# campaign and decided to file a rape case against the accuse.

she said that since then the accuse blackmail/threaten her and committed rape on her several time added that the accuse even call her to his office (office of assistant director handloom) after 4 pm wherein the accuse committed rape on her within the said government office complex situated within new dc office complex kishtwar also hoisting office of the deputy commissioner kishtwar. 
#gediroutekishtwar1 #kishtwar #rapevictim

text:
how metoo movement started ? meet the founder tarana burke, the woman who started the me too movement a-decade ago - 
#metoo, an online campaign that supports the survivors of sexual abuse, assault and harrassment, has recently taken social media by storm. although it has gained popularity over the last two months, the initiative actually began 10 years ago. 
tarana burke, an activist from harlem, launched the movement a decade ago to aid underprivileged women of color affected by sexual abuse. 
she was inspired after bonding with a young girl during a youth camp hosted by just be inc., a nonprofit she founded that’s “focused on the health, well-being, and wholeness of young women of color,” the site reads. 
burke detailed the encounter on the site. she said the girl revealed her mother’s boyfriend had been abusing her. that’s when burke decided to take action by helping the communities where rape crisis centers and sexual assault workers were not present, and “me too” was born. "it's not about a viral campaign for me. it’s about a movement," she told cnn. "on one side, it's a bold declarative statement that 'i'm not ashamed' and 'i'm not alone.' on the other side, it's a statement from survivor to survivor that says 'i see you, i hear you, i understand you and i'm here for you or i get it.'" the two-word phrase resurfaced in october when actress alyssa milano took to twitter to invite those who have experienced sexual harrassment to respond with “me too.” her tweet followed the new york times’ oct. 5 investigation into decades of sexual harassment allegations against hollywood producer harvey weinstein, and within hours #metoo went viral on twitter, facebook, instagram and beyond as people took to the platforms to share their personal accounts of sexual assault. 
by the end of that weekend morning, more than 40,000 people had responded to her tweet. more than 12 million people had engaged with the hashtag across facebook and twitter, cnn reported. 
ms burke was one of those named time magazine's person of the year.

as the campaign picked up speed, journalist britni danielle applauded burke on twitter for starting the campaign.

text:
i usually don't expose my life on instagram, but tonight i am feeling angry and i need to do it, but first, i need to ask, how many people, at least once in their life, felt like they were obliged to say yes because they were manipulated or because they already had said no a hundred time and they felt that they could say it a million times or more it wouldn't change anything , so they gave up and said yes? i sincerely hope it's only me, but i know it isn't. i know i am not the only one feeling like this and that's why i am talking about it tonight, because i think it's unfair, because it drives me crazy to think that this happened to other people.
this situation happened to me a lot, but i will always remember two times that changed my whole life. twice in my life someone didn't ask for my permission or didn't listen when i said no and didn't stopped when i pushed him. twice in my life i felt disgusting and dirty because someone decided his desires were more important than mine. twice in my life someone didn't understand that if you don't say yes that means no and that no means no. twice in my life, i felt powerless and responsible for someone's action on my body. i hated myself for so long after that because i thought i deserved it and i couldn't talk about it, i thought people would hate me, that my mom wouldn't love me anymore, but i am telling you, this is all false. i recently told my mom about it and she still loves me, and i realized, a year later, that it wasn't my fault and that it's never going to be the victim's fault, even though you "seemed to want it" or even though you thought you wanted it at some point. it's not your fault. so tonight i am talking about it hoping that it will make you talk about it, hoping it will help you go through that and i am telling you guys, you are not alone.
so, talk about it and you'll feel better, each time i talk about  it i feel better and i think we should all talk about it more because the people that do those actions are hiding behind our silence. so guys, please talk about it❤️
#rapecamebeforeminiskirts #sharinglove #silenceisnttheanswer #metoo

text:
on friday, i went to pick up the copic markers i ordered with my local art supplies shop and tested them in my sketchbook. those are the colors my mind associate with july, so expect an art nouveau inspired portrait in those tones to illustrate my 2019 calendar. i use my sketchbook to try out my markers and experiment with hairstyles and shading as the more i draw those cartoony portraits, the more i enjoy them. 
you may not know it, but my fine art teacher in art major high school was the one to disgust me from portraits painting. first because like most art school teachers he was a snob who told me that unless i can reproduce the work of renaissance masters i would get nowhere. 
then because he was a pervert, pig and all round asshole who graded his female students  based on the depth of their cleavage and sexy looking clothes. i pushed him aside then he tried to hold me by the waste and this self preservation move ensured that he found every opportunity to criticise my work and flunk me. 
all the girls in the school knew about his perverse moves, and what should be described as molestation now, yet we were all discouraged to report him. 
i stayed away from people drawing for close to 25 years...and this is one of my #metoo stories because he sadly wasn’t the first or the last 😢 .
💦
💦
💦

text:
“no one can make you feel inferior without your consent”. this quote is often credited to eleanor roosevelt, but is actually an interpretation from the media of a perceived “snub” by another woman. .
in times of increasing awareness, ignorance and hypocrisy are encouraged. and in the fight for women’s equality and safety (human rights), it’s crippling our forces from within: between our own sisters. the front against us is still strong (as demonstrated by recent events), and benefitting from our infighting. .
how much of what we do and say, is a learned behavior from a societal construct subconsciously clung to? how many of those actions can you actually recognize in yourself? how many women vehemently defend patriarchy, in the name of safety, finances, and “status”? how many are unaware that they have been blinded?  how many are aware, but yet undermine other women due to pure survival instinct, or worse: a choice of luxury?  how many self-proclaimed feminist “sisters” understand only that they want things to be better for them, personally, but their actions contradict their own proclamations of feminist dedication for the whole? how many claim feminism for ego or appearances, yet tear other women down in subtle ways, attempting to assert superiority alone or in a pack, through gaslighting,  projection, and sabotage? how many have ingrained in them “competition fever”, a deeply seated, unconscious predisposition to take-down other women they see as a “threat”? how many times have you heard from a female friend: “women are crazy” “this is why i’m friends with guys” or “you’re asking for it getting involved with women”. how many times have you shrugged those statements off? how many times have you said them yourself? .
we cannot win this battle with a divided front, divided only by our response to the influence of our established system of patriarchy. so i say to you, women: never let anyone, including another woman, or group of women, allow you to feel inferior. in addition to this, cease any thoughts to as if another woman is inferior to yourself. ask these hard questions and demand these actions of yourself and others, for the good of us all.

text:
who was ada lovelace? –she was the 19th century mathematician and writer who wrote the first algorithm intended to be carried out by a machine.
–she was the first computer programmer.
–she was the only legitimate child of lord byron.
–she was a countess.
–charles babbage (creator of the analytical engine) called her the ‘enchantress of numbers.’
–she was the world’s first debugger.
–she suggested that computers could one day effect society, or be used as a collaborative tool.
–she had a gambling problem and formed a gambling syndicate and created a mathematical model for placing large bets.
in other words, she was an amazing innovator!
thanks to ada lovelace for her contribution to the mathematical world.
her dreams can be your dreams.

text:
औरतों-लड़कियों और बच्चियों पर अत्याचार हो रहा देश में लोगों की रोजीरोटी छीनी गई है लोग अब ज़हर खानेपर मजबूर हैं 4-6 महीनों में इलेक्शन होने हैं उस पर से ध्यान हटाकर #metoo #metoo खेला जा रहा है अरे सीधी बात है अगर आप पर यौन उत्पीड़न हुआ है तो 10-12 साल बाद ही क्यों नींद खुली के हमे इंसाफ चाहिए हमपर यौन उत्पीड़न-शोषण हुआ है, हमे घूरा गया है, अभी ही याद आया है .
अगर किसी पर अत्याचार हुआ है तो मेरे देशवासियों ने तबतब उस पीड़िता को न्याय दिलाने के लिए रौद्ररूप लिया है और उस पीड़िता को न्याय दिलाया है.
आप जैसी औरतों की वजह से हमारे समाज में बच्चियों तक को नहीं बक्शा जा रहा ये #metoo नही बल्कि #badnaamkartoo है.

text: sisters, we stand together in solidarity on #blackfridays to fight for change. we fight for our right to tell the truth and be heard. something that is really important to remember is that in order to make change we need to be educated. if you are enraged and you’re thinking to yourself “what can i do to help?” “how can i make change?” educate. learn the facts about sexual assault look at the statistics and learn everything you can and then spread the word. tell the people around you what you’ve learned. knowledge is powerful and educating those around you about sexual assault can have an extremely powerful impact. we will no longer be silent on this topic. i really suggest watching the hunting ground on netflix, it speaks about sexual assault on college campuses specifically, its extremely powerful and terrifying. #breakthesilence #drford #anitahill #webelieveyou #trustwomen #timesup #metoo #believeallsurvivors #bethechangeyouwanttosee #knowthefacts #blackfridays #ragetochange #womenempowerment #makechange #voteblue #registertovote

text:
my friend told me about mental health awareness month. 
honestly around this time of the year i find more difficult to deal with difficult people and keep my smile which is usually am more low 🔑 or try be around close group of friends who let me be me. i also usually increase my psychologist appointments around this time of the year and decrease the amount of stressful interactions i have with people.

to everyone who ever feels like they need mental help. i will say this much. it’s okay. please go seek it. do it for yourself. you don’t need permission. taking care of your mental heath is just as important as your physical health.
even though i can function relatively well in society i am man enough to say i have many flaws and am human and sometime reality becomes overwhelming for me to handle on my own. i have a high threshold for dealing with dis function but i am very aware maintenance on psyche is necessary.
that being said. please take care of yourselves and it’s okay 👌 to seek help.

text:
regrann from @suds.muse -  to be a woman and truly belong in the world: nadia murad’s nobel peace prize, one-year of #metoo and all the debate around shifting gender power-dynamics: my mind is in a flux! we are making some progress for sure - in terms of making this world a fairer place for women (essentially half-of-humanity, a fact which somehow tends to get lost). but the cost - oh the cost of this numbingly slow progress!
.
i have been reading a lot about nadia murad and dr. mukwege (joint recipients of the nobel). nadia murad’s journey is harrowing and of inhuman courage: from being a prisoner-slave of is while her people were being systematically exterminated, to a lucky-escape, to recounting her painful experience to the world while holding on to the hope of justice. i hope she wins in her staggering battle against blatant genocide in the name of ideology (which i shall never understand). and every other woman - in her struggle, trivial or grand. we owe a fairer world to our children. [portraits from kumaon - 2, ramgarh, 28.09.2018]
.
.
.
.
.

text:
the new wells and wong is out, and i finished reading it last week and squeed at warya over whatsapp at an ungodly hour in the morning.  there are so many things i love about this book- its use of shakespeare and the theatre; daisy and hazel's changing relationship as they grow up and learn to verbalise hurts (hazel) and hold space better (daisy); how queerness and race and privilege are treated in the world of the books. the detective society is growing up and it is becoming increasingly hard to use the invisibility of childhood to their advantage, especially as they're beginning to come up against the expectations of ladylike behaviour. 
there was a terrifying, believable moment of near violence from a character who had earlier demonstrated a capacity for hurting women, and reading it right in the middle of the turbulence of #metoo and familiar names being outed as abusers hit me hard. stevens doesn't need to make angels of women either, and there is a brilliant section early on where hazel's understanding of one of the characters slowly unfurls as she learns to see beyond the performative niceness to what the person really is like. 
#pipreads #instaread #bookstagram #wellsandwong #deathinthespotlight

text:
carmilla (laertes ' "little sister" in the film the giaour) called herself millarca when she courted general spielsdorf's niece. in life, she was known as mircalla (my russian-speaking friend broke it down for me as "mir" = world, peace, and "calla" = lily). in the ny alt.end i wrote in 2015, she was to call herself lamirca (ok, there is another "l" but that would look like llama). .

so i went to bed thinking if there was any way i can suggest karma, as she is the huntress of sexual predators. .

in the morning, i heard laertes whisper: "ill carma." (the drawing is from 2016.) 🌹

text:
such a tremendous honor to be in the house for this final night of antigone in ferguson developed by theater of war productions as a tool to discuss race, social justice, and healing through a staged reading featuring well known actors alongside a chorus of police officers, activists, youth, teachers, and more from ferguson, missouri and new york. powerful and moving are a tremendous understatement. the energy in the room was impassioned, the music gave me chills, life, and hope. the conversation afterwards left all with the intention to do better for ourselves, and better for each other. two bonuses - the joy on the face of @eisadavis while singing, and @chrisnothofficial in the role of creon, the failing ruler blinded by power, played with cartoon-like evil fervor. another great night in nyc.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
dear women (and men), to be honest i was the part of those who were in disbelief. not because i did not have faith with women who have been sharing stories of the assaults and the harassment they have faced, but because, i had so little faith in the world already, that i did not want to lose it. the past one week has been brutal. with men and women, women even more so because of the kind of experiences they have let out namely and anonymously that i can feel, quite literally their broken worlds.

while at one side i believe that there should be a clear understanding of what does sexual assault apertains to, what it constitutes of and what it doesn't; metoo campaign like a lot of other hashtags is not a trend that every woman coming out brave, to this world is following. it is in all its senses a way to put forth what wrongdoings have been faced by them under one tag. that too only for this world to pick up the scattered pieces at one place. women do not, i repeat for emphasis, do not know anyone shit and hence we get to decide when, in what day of the week and what year of the calendar do we speak about the horrifying experiences that we have had and make 'our' monsters face the world.

the stories i've read in the past few days have made me feel naked, ripped off my sanity at times and have tangled my flesh and skin together. such is the harrowing experience women have had and i'll take time to feel like myself and start living with it again.

until then, i'm saluting women who are fighting, juggling home, assignments, projects, deadlines and the shockwaves of the metoo movement around them. my heart is going out to all of you, anywhere you are in the world while you are jotting down with a continuous struggle the accounts of sexual harassment and the nude incidents that have occurred to you by those in power.

let's look forward to reparations. i am here. he is here. we are here. we are all listening and we know, we know, that this was not your fault. so keep drinking water and keep rioting.

thank you for doing what you are doing. i know what it is, i know what it feels like.

yours in believe, 
today and ten years later.
shruti(@finite.difference) 
#metoo

until then, i am saluting women who are fighting, juggling home, assignments, projects, deadlines and the shockwaves of the metoo movement around them. my hea is going out to all of you, anywhere you are in the world while you are jotting down with a continuous struggle the accounts of sexual harassment and the nude incidents that have occurred to you by those in power.

let's look forward to reparations. i am here. he is here. we are here. we are all listening and we know, we know, that this was not your fault. so keep drinking water and keep rioting.

thank you for doing what you are doing. i know what it is, i know what it feels like.

yours in believe, 
today and ten years later.

text:
went on a hike with the brosef today. i spent a lot of time thinking, him a lot of time farting. .
.
.
but i was happy to spend time with this dude. happy for the support that he has given me all these years. happy to reflect on everything that has happened in my life and what has brought me to the point where i’m at today. .
.
about 4 years ago i went through something horrific. something i never truly dealt with ... until now. due to what happened to me, i spiraled into a deep depression. for those who have had depression, you know it’s not something you can just “snap out of”. it doesn’t work like that. it affects your ability to even do the most basic tasks, to think properly, to do physical activity.
i lived in denial for a long time. i thought i could fight it. i thought if my mind was strong enough, i could beat this thing. but depression is like any illness. it needs treatment. thanks to a few friends and @brian_gentry , i finally got the help that i needed. 
#mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness #depression #ptsd #mentalhealthstigma #mentalhealthmatters #anxiety #mentalhealthsupport #metoo

text:
when it comes to the non-family females in my life, @ms.shell has been around the longest. what michelle might not know is that she is the last female friend i still have from before my assault.

we met during a very fun, creative, and joyful time in my life. we were both working at walt disney world in 2005, and were on the same shift at magic kingdom. michelle said something "rocks my face" and i yelled from across the room "thats amazing, im using that. you rock my face!" and boom, we were friends. when our schedules paired us up, we had a hilarious time working together. later on in our friendship, we both got jobs at a restaurant. while i was working there, my assault happened. michelle was one of my best friends and i didn't tell her, or anyone for that matter. shortly thereafter, i switched restaurants, switched majors, got accepted at usf, and moved to tampa. we stayed connected on social but she didn't miss much from my tampa chapter. that was post-trauma, pre-healing and the beginning of my coping mechanism: study hard, work hard, party harder. this also translated to my pr career in chicago.

the last time i saw this beautiful soul in person was when i came to la for a campaign launch for a client in 2010. she came to the launch event, after which we went back to the bar at the hotel i was staying at and proceeded to catch up on what had happened since 2006. we talked for hours and hours as if no time had passed. i flew home to chicago the next day and wouldn't get to smoosh this face again until last night. almost nine years later. and it wasn't for a lack of trying. since barry and i moved to socal in 2011, michelle and i have been ships passing in the night with our schedules, staying connected and up to date through social. 
looking back, i'm glad it took this long for us to reconnect in person. not only did it feel like no time had passed, again, but the last time i felt this incredible was when we were friends, before my assault. to have her in the front row, as close to me as possible, on the first night of this tour, where i share my survivor story, meant the whole world to me. my heart is so full. thank you for seeing me, michelle. 💛

text:
#believewomen #metoo #mentoo 
there's been a lot of talk lately about sexual violence in the media. it's something i usually never shy away from talking. but this current narrative has made me mainly sit in a state of pondering over this issue. 
i read an article written by a woman and said she was sexually assaulted, but she didn't want people to take her word for it. she went on to say that just throwing someone in jail, or even just demonizing them can destroy the fabric of life. 
i respected her thoughts as a survivor, but it made me think even more. 
i'm not a famous activist like @therealmariskahargitay or speaker like @elizabeth_smart_official but the survivors i have personally talked to, friends and strangers alike, aren't seeking justice or revenge. they just want to be heard. 
like me, they never want to be the same air as their abuser ever again. 
i believe in 'innocent until proven guilty" but that's a thing that prevents people from getting thrown in jail.
imagine your best friend in the entire world comes to you and says they've been raped. would you believe them or just say "i need more evidence?" what if you child says this to you? 
i've had a friend tell me she was raped right after it happened. she asked me to come to the hospital when she was at. 
i agreed to go, no questions asked. 
as i sat in silence with her waiting for the nurse to do the rape kit. as she silently sobbed in her bed, i thought about what monster would do this to her. 
i didn't even remotely think "innocent until proven guilty" 
i did the same thing as she went to testify in court. 
when we say "believe women" we aren't saying to lock them up. just hear what they have to say. if you don't believe them, keep it to yourself and let the system work itself out. or whatever. 
cause if a man has even one accusation against them, i'd hold the children in my life a little closer when they are around. i definitely wouldn't want them on #scotus or as president. 
and you say "accusations destroy lives!" but well, look what's going on. look who still got nominated, and who's the president.  look who are still bishops and priests? 
#nomore
name: Holley Noelle Robison

text: more than the experiences that are coming out because of the #metoo movement in india, it is the reactions of some of the arm chair pandits that shock me... especially questions like why is tanushree dutta speaking up now?? if she is so innocent, why was she comfortable doing intimate scenes with emraan hashmi?? for starters, the difference is ‘choice’ and ‘force’.... just because she chooses to do it with one actor, does not mean she should be forced to do the same with another.. to elaborate, if a sex worker who prostitutes herself for a living is forced to do the same to satisfy someone’s ego and pleasure, then it is a rape... the victim being a sex worker does not diminish the severity of that crime.. just because a woman drinks, smokes, dresses in non traditional clothes or lives with a man without marriage, it does not mean that anyone can touch her without her permission!! no matter when someone chooses to speak, hear them... give them a fair trial!! #metoo #metoomovement #metooindia #tanushreedutta #vintananda #safetouch #nomeansno

text:
ok so i’ve gotten a lot of dms over my story. so let’s talk about it. why was that first kiss between sierra and jamey in #sierraburgessisaloser so incredibly wrong? so wrong that it borders on assault?
this kiss, despite what teenage girls may think, was not romantic. you see, jamey had no idea it was sierra he was kissing. one minute veronica was standing in front of him. he was ordered to close his eyes. sierra appeared (from underneath a car?!) and places her hands on his eyes, in effect blinding him. in today’s day and age, in the day of #metoo and #timesup this is not acceptable. 
just because sierra is not “classically” attractive, an underdog who eventually got picked by the hot guy does not make this ok. 
just because it was a girl who tricked a boy into kissing her, does not make this ok. 
definition of rape by deception: rape by deception is a crime in which the perpetrator has the victim's agreement and compliance, but gains it through deception or fraudulent statements or actions.
jamey did not give his #consent to kiss sierra. and to have them kiss at the end, and him quip “hey, have we done this before?” is nope remotely funny. it’s sickening and it’s wrong. happy to discuss if anyone has any opposing viewpoints. cheers.
#feminism #equalrights #equality #notok @ncentineo @shannonpurser @thad.luckinbill @dappertoad

text:
🍃the #metoo movement has taken the country by storm and i m glad that women are finally getting the courage to stand up. although i believe the ratio is still very low coz i don’t think so there is any woman who has faced any kind of unwanted advances in her life ! this movement i feel is the real #swatchbharatabhiyaan 😊
.
.
🍃as a woman and as a mom i feel that it’s one ‘s responsibility to teach our boys to respect . men should be taught to respect women and should be ingrained in their minds from the childhood. most of the indian men have been raised without being taught this lil thing and what they learn is from peers and society  and get confused with what’s the right way to behave. .
.
🍃with my small impact and voice  my earnest request to all the men is to listen to your partners, sisters , girlfriends and friends and be empathetic towards them. don’t try to brush any small incidents under the carpet and try to understand what it’s like to face such situations and deal with them everyday! .
.
🍃women out there please do not hesitate to come out and speak up! every single voice counts and don’t ever feel that succumbing to a situation is the best possible solution. be brave and fight it out and try to seek help from everyone. not all guys are bad. give people a chance to understand . .
.
🍃most importantly for everyone be a good human being . start caring about each other. be better in what you are doing. you may not know everything but there is no harm is trying to learn and being empathetic towards each other ! .
.
i have been feeling too strongly about this movement and hence wrote a post on it! i stand up and salute all the girls who have come forward to fight for this cause ! .
.
.
.
#naarishakti #womenempowerment #istandupforallwomenworldwide #respectwomen #maashakti #durgamaa #durgapuja #teachyoursonstorespectwomen #womensupportingwomen #betterhumans

text:
tw: sexual assault
.
four — i remember laying on my teenage cousins bed and crying, staring at his darth maul poster. my mom confirmed it later, when she told me she was surprised i was so comfortable around him considering what had happened when i was little. 
fifteen — the boy i liked pushed me up against a tree and left me dirty, crying, naked and alone in the woods. no one at school believed me until he tried to hit me at a party when i drunkenly confronted him, and my friends had to hold him back. 
sixteen — an adult man who added me on facebook promised to take me to my favorite science museum, but we just ended up in his hotel room. i didn’t realize until i was much older how taken advantage i was by someone who was an adult. 
seventeen — i became extremely close with my twenty three year old cousin when i was sixteen. nothing seemed wrong with his daily calls and texts for over a year until he came to visit when i drunkenly fell asleep and woke up with him on top of me. i cried and made it out from under him, locking my door before crying myself to sleep. for the rest of his visit, i begged my friends to stick around and make sure i was sober and safe before leaving. the moment that they left, he forced me to drink a drugged gin and tonic. i don’t remember much. when i confronted him he said that i had wanted it, and i that no one would believe me if i told. i haven’t been to a family event since. 
eighteen — a boy at a party let me cut him in line for the bathroom, then followed me in and locked the door. he forced me down, but i started to scream until my friend broke the door down. 
twenty one — a supervisor at camp — my favorite place in the world — ripped off my favorite dress and didn’t listen as i bled and cried and begged for him to stop. the next summer he was fired for sexually harassing a sixteen year old counselor that i supervised, and i thanked her for doing what i couldn’t. i still can’t shake the guilt that i could have prevented it if i’d reported it sooner. .
.

my circle is very small and they know i love being behind the scenes. i rather see those i love in the spotlight and i don't have to worry about looking "perfect" for anyone... i love my rough edges and one of my perfect evenings is home writing and inventing..... but i am so thankful to call each of these ladies my friends and inspirations. if i'm going to be out its with them. we are all different with a common thread of wanting to see each other succeed.  thanks ladies. ..💜💜💜💜

text:
guilt, selfishness, and shame: these tend to plague the minds of many people in my life when we talk about why they don’t create time for themselves. 😫😟😖
how do you feel when you consider taking time for yourself? does it sound impossible? selfish? shameful? do you feel like you don’t deserve it? do you consider others to be more important? maybe you tell yourself it’s unnecessary? -
-
i want you to know the truth:•you do deserve it•you do need it•you do have time for it•
-
-
me time allows you to recharge and cope with stress. taking breaks can help with stress resilience, focus, & energy levels. me time is critical if time and energy are important to you. and what you choose is up to you! a workout, listening to music, reading, a bath, art....whatever makes you feel good and gives you time to recharge. ❤️
-
👧🏼👧🏾👦🏽think about the young ones in your life. the ones near and dear to your heart. they’re watching. and they learn by example. would you want them to feel like they had to sacrifice every part of themselves to make others happy? unlikely. you deserve the same. love yo’self.
-
-
🙌🏼💪🏽😃rest makes you more effective. our world puts a huge emphasis on ‘busy’, but being busy is not something to be proud of if you are not allowing yourself time to enjoy yourself. it’s better to do less, with more love and attention, while also taking time for yourself. -
-
you cannot pour from an empty cup. instead of serving everyone and everything first and hoping you’ll have enough of something left over for yourself, fill you up and your energy, love, compassion, excitement, etc will overflow into the lives of those around you.
-
i love you. now, you need to stay loving you. ❤️
-
-
me time worksheet coming soon! ❤️ -
-
-

in case you haven’t heard, salty (the bloody brilliant feminist sex & relationships newsletter for women, trans and non-binary people that i have been raving about) has had their instagram account disabled and i am disgusted. three months ago, salty brought to light the violent sexual abuse allegations against musician william control from the band aiden. quoting from the latest newsletter salty says “our editors personally spoke with six of his alleged victims; who allege rape, beating, financial extortion, creating and sharing non consensual pornographic photos and tattoo branding (branding their genitalia to prove ownership) all under the guise of bdsm. we believe these women.” the alleged abuser then asked his followers to flag salty’s instagram until it was taken down. i stand with survivors and i stand with salty @instagram we demand for salty to be reinstated #bringbacksalty #salty #saltyworld #williamcontrolaltdelete #believewomen #metoo

text:
women talking by miriam toews
genre - fiction but stemming from a real crime
style - in some ways august is the narrator, the one trustworthy man assigned the task of documenting the women’s meetings, the novel is conveyed through transcription which is surprisingly immersive and thought provoking
high point - the way the voices of the women come through despite a society’s attempt to silence them, the metafictional moments and humour that lighten a book on a very heavy topic
low point - that the women have learnt that “molotschna animals are safer than molotschna women, and better cared for.”
take away -  the power of talk, the power of women talking! 
important interview and re the actual case https://www.theguardian.com/books/2018/aug/18/miriam-toews-interview-women-talking-mennonite

text:
#decolonialbiznessworld is all about you as a business #visionary. it is about you tapping into your greatest self as a #healer and you using everyday business operations and strategic planning to amplify #love as the world's most natural currency and directly relieve pain.

decolonial because we aim to #decolonize and #regenerate. bizness because #hiphop, for many folks, provides a blueprint for radical transformation. world because we share one global #ecosystem, and #mothernature needs us to honor her gifts and recognize them alongside our own.

decolonial bizness world is made for the #magicians of the global economy, those of us who have been forced to the margins of capitalist accumulation, while serving its masters and everyday beneficiaries. we have been made marginal even as we remain #theglobalmajority.

and we're done serving the masters' delusions and everyday violence. #timesup. #neveragain. #blacklivesmatter. #niunamenos. #prisonstrike. #mniwiconi. we rise up as one to repair the damage born of five centuries of violence and delusion as well as the violent systems that created #imperialism.

did you know that democracy was founded on three main ideas: militarism, private property, and slavery? if you didn't know that, it is because you too have been colonized. we're all in this together. everyone. #metoo.

decolonial bizness world uses stories and #symbols to teach everyday business operations such as #accounting, #distribution, and #marketing from the standpoint of ecological resilience and #belovedcommunity.

martin luther king, jr. defined beloved community as one made of people coming together for racial #healing, #peace, and shared #wealth. these values we hold and share. we are true love's #shareholders: we aim to end slavery, abolish prisons and borders, and create the conditions for true beloved community and #sacredsexuality.

text:
a couple of weeks ago @longdistancelovebombs and i were chatting about what's going on in the world today and about the #metoo movement.
•
we both decided we had to take the courageous leap to get uncomfortable and step out of our space of privilege and risk saying the wrong thing, so we could learn what getting it right might mean or even look like. we accepted the invitations we received from women and brilliant writers and leaders like @glennondoyle - @danielledoby - @sophiabush - my lady @beingisbeautiful - to show up and use our voices to talk about how we, as men, can get curious about what's going on and help in whatever way we can.
click on the link in my bio to listen to the podcast we recorded!
•
it was scary, vulnerable and a lot of fun too. i love all of my amazing co-createthelovers on here and i appreciate you calling me forward into this space. i am a big proponent of always living and loving on our edge... so here's my edge. super appreciative to jeremy aka @longdistancelovebombs for stepping off the cliff and on a couple of landmines with me.
•
click on the link in my bio and listen to the podcast we recorded. please give him a 5 star review :), subscribe, share, and leave a comment below about your thoughts and what you liked and what we could do differently/better. lots of love to you all. #createthelove

text:
some days are easy. some are hard. today we fought. but then he apologized. and so did i. then we held hands. then the toddler cried all afternoon. then i bathed in valor and cbd oil. then he built a fire so we could make smores.

now is not forever. thank you, god, for my healthy family, a stable roof over our heads, a reliable vehicle, food in our pantry, and comfy beds to sleep in.

text:
undeniably, false allegations of sexual violence is likely to inflict reputational ramifications on the falsely accused and i sympathise with them. however, as it’s difficult for experts to calculate precise statistics, research has suggested only between 2-10% of all sexual assault reports are falsified, which is a percentage that has remained invariably and consistently low. subscribing to the narrative that false allegations are rampant and therefore a universal threat to all men is frankly fearmongering. as those reporting false allegations are overrepresented in media, these anomalies are used to discredit victims of sexual violence and the existence of rape culture.
stop holding survivors who are brave enough to share their stories with the world responsible for the statistically low number of liars with vindictive agendas, which hinders their quest for justice.

text:
true confessions
.
some give credentials, i give confessions.
.
i’m here in the hopes of proving to you that your very life, is art. that right inside the mess of your broken heart, or in the mistakes, in the clashing, in the loss… is the greatest art of it all.
.
that discovery is where i’ve found my relief.
.
i’ve had so many things stripped away in my life, as surely you have, and the beauty in that is that any inauthenticity seems to get stripped out right along with it. any striving to be perceived as something special dies very fast, when things suddenly get very real.
.
and so, i’ve decided to get naked for you! naked with my relationship with life, up until this point…
.
transformation occurs when we bring creative expression to the scene of any pain.
so over the next many weeks, i’ll be unlocking myself from my past through creative play before you. and my hope is that you’ll unlock things within yourself that have long been awaiting their license to be felt, so that you may find some deeper freedom, too.
.
the first confession will be posted next week.
.
here’s to the empowerment available us all when we have the courage to play hard.
.
head to my highlight about for more!
.
love,
sherry
🧡
.
.
.
.

text:
me too. .
.
i was 8 years old and i was being taken care of by someone my parents trusted with my life. instead of fun and games and memories to look back on, i was betrayed and sexually assaulted. .
.
when you ask me about my childhood everything centers around the age of 8. i can’t remember much before or after or i confuse  things and think i was 8. without pictures to remind me of things i would never remember them at all. .
.
because of this became a secret keeper at a very young age. i became afraid of trusting men. i became defensive and always felt like i had to look out for myself. i became angry. i felt alone. i had trouble connecting with others. i had a hard time letting people in. .
.
i am learning to change became into was and most importantly i am learning to forgive. i cannot change the past and i am not sharing this to call my abuser out. i am sharing this to continue to educate people that you cannot judge a book by its cover. .
.
my story is not a highlight reel of positive memories, smiles and laughter. there are dark moments, memories and experiences. they are all part of me and they all contributed to who i was. but the amazing thing is that i control who i become from this day forward. .
.
i am stronger, confident and braver for sharing this. i am happy, loving, beautiful and inspiring because i choose to be. .
.
if something similar happened to you i want you to know you are strong and beautiful. it’s not your fault. you never deserved it. nobody has the right to tell you how to handle this. you don’t owe anything to anyone. .
.
i am melody and i am here for you. xoxo

text:
di tengah isu #metoo yang masih memanas di india, beredar sebuah kabar menghebohkan yang melibatkan produser film bernama karim morani. pengusaha yang juga sahabat shahrukh khan itu baru saja dilaporkan ke polisi oleh seorang perempuan atas kasus dugaan pemerkosaan.

dilansir dari bollywoodlife.com, korban melaporkan karim ke polisi atas beberapa kasus. yang pertama adalah pemerkosaan yang disebut berlangsung pada tahun 2015 silam.

korban yang tak membuka identitasnya mengungkap apa yang kala itu ia alami bersama produser film chennai expressdan ra.one tersebut. kala itu, karim sedang berada di gedung yang sama dengan shahrukh khan, varun dhawan dan sutradara rohit shetty.

1. morani ambil gambar tak senonoh

sebelum melakukan pemerkosaan, korban menyebut karim morani sudah pernah melakukan pelecehan seksual terhadapnya. tak hanya itu, produser yang berbasis di delhi ini juga memotretnya dengan kondisi tak senonoh.

foto itu kemudian dijadikan morani sebagai senjata untuk mengancamnya. morani selalu mengancam untuk menyebarkan foto itu ke keluarga jika korban tak memenuhi permintaan produser ini.

2. dapat ancaman "morani meneleponku dan bilang ia ingin aku datang ke sana. kubilang tidak bisa, karena ada keluargaku. tapi dia mengancamku kalau ia akan menyebarkan foto itu ke keluargaku. aku berbohong, dan akhirnya datang. ketika di sana, ia tak mengizinkanku keluar dari kamar dan mengunciku di dalam. aku berada di lantai paling atas, dan ruangan di sana berbentuk zig-zag, tidak lurus. dia bilang kalau kamar itu bersebelahan dengan shahrukh khan, varun dhawan dan rohit shetty," ujar korban.

tak bisa berkutik, akhirnya korban hanya diam di kamar dan tidak bisa pergi ke mana-mana. sampai pada akhirnya morani kembali datang dan membawa minuman keras bersamanya.
.

tweet_full:
di tengah isu #metoo yang masih memanas di india, beredar sebuah kabar menghebohkan yang melibatkan produser film bernama karim morani. pengusaha yang juga sahabat shahrukh khan itu baru saja dilaporkan ke polisi oleh seorang perempuan atas kasus dugaan pemerkosaan.

dilansir dari bollywoodlife.com, korban melaporkan karim ke polisi atas beberapa kasus. yang pertama adalah pemerkosaan yang disebut berlangsung pada tahun 2015 silam.

korban yang tak membuka identitasnya mengungkap apa yang kala itu ia alami bersama produser film chennai expressdan ra.one tersebut. kala itu, karim sedang berada di gedung yang sama dengan shahrukh khan, varun dhawan dan sutradara rohit shetty.

1. morani ambil gambar tak senonoh

sebelum melakukan pemerkosaan, korban menyebut karim morani sudah pernah melakukan pelecehan seksual terhadapnya. tak hanya itu, produser yang berbasis di delhi ini juga memotretnya dengan kondisi tak senonoh.

foto itu kemudian dijadikan morani sebagai senjata untuk mengancamnya. morani selalu mengancam untuk menyebarkan foto itu ke keluarga jika korban tak memenuhi permintaan produser ini.

2. dapat ancaman "morani meneleponku dan bilang ia ingin aku datang ke sana. kubilang tidak bisa, karena ada keluargaku. tapi dia mengancamku kalau ia akan menyebarkan foto itu ke keluargaku. aku berbohong, dan akhirnya datang. ketika di sana, ia tak mengizinkanku keluar dari kamar dan mengunciku di dalam. aku berada di lantai paling atas, dan ruangan di sana berbentuk zig-zag, tidak lurus. dia bilang kalau kamar itu bersebelahan dengan shahrukh khan, varun dhawan dan rohit shetty," ujar korban.

tak bisa berkutik, akhirnya korban hanya diam di kamar dan tidak bisa pergi ke mana-mana. sampai pada akhirnya morani kembali datang dan membawa minuman keras bersamanya.
.
geser lanjutan caption
.
.

source by: kapanlagi .
.

.

text: i did not stay out of the forest. admittedly, it wasn’t a good idea. i am saddened by the fact that just walking to the end of a winding forest boardwalk alone on public land is considered an act of resistance. i don’t live in a world that is safe. i longed so much to see the lake and not just the parking lot, that i literally risked my life to see it. one could probably argue that to think that somebody may be lying in wait for me in the thick brush and freezing bog is completely irrational. maybe. i ran to the end of the boardwalk just to see what was at the end of the path, and stole a few moments before running back to my car. the same way i used to run and jump into my bed as a kid because i was afraid of what was underneath. what i feared then is the same as what i fear now. #metoo
name: Stephanie Centeno

text:
nu är det 1 år sedan #metoo och jag skulle kunna skriva så mycket men jag väljer kritiken om att feminister ser sig som offer.

jag tänker att offer är inget man väljer att vara utan något man är. om man varit utsatt så har man varit ett offer, men det tyder inte på någon svaghet. styrka kan vara så mycket, och kvinnors o ickemäns organisering och solidaritet iochmed #metoo är styrka. att säga vi har fått nog - är en styrka.

det känns så konstigt att feminism påstås göra kvinnor till offer eller svaga när det är feminism som gjort mig till någon som ej tar skit, tror på mig själv och har en jävla självrespekt. när någon trampar på mig så hugger jag😂

text:
di tengah isu #metoo yang masih memanas di india, beredar sebuah kabar menghebohkan yang melibatkan produser film bernama karim morani. pengusaha yang juga sahabat shahrukh khan itu baru saja dilaporkan ke polisi oleh seorang perempuan atas kasus dugaan pemerkosaan.

dilansir dari bollywoodlife.com, korban melaporkan karim ke polisi atas beberapa kasus. yang pertama adalah pemerkosaan yang disebut berlangsung pada tahun 2015 silam

korban yang tak membuka identitasnya mengungkap apa yang kala itu ia alami bersama produser film chennai express dan ra.one tersebut. kala itu, karim sedang berada di gedung yang sama dengan shahrukh khan, varun dhawan dan sutradara rohit shetty.

sebelum melakukan pemerkosaan, korban menyebut karim morani sudah pernah melakukan pelecehan seksual terhadapnya. tak hanya itu, produser yang berbasis di delhi ini juga memotretnya dengan kondisi tak senonoh.

foto itu kemudian dijadikan morani sebagai senjata untuk mengancamnya. morani selalu mengancam untuk menyebarkan foto itu ke keluarga jika korban tak memenuhi permintaan produser ini.
.
"morani meneleponku dan bilang ia ingin aku datang ke sana. kubilang tidak bisa, karena ada keluargaku. tapi dia mengancamku kalau ia akan menyebarkan foto itu ke keluargaku. aku berbohong, dan akhirnya datang. ketika di sana, ia tak mengizinkanku keluar dari kamar dan mengunciku di dalam. aku berada di lantai paling atas, dan ruangan di sana berbentuk zig-zag, tidak lurus. dia bilang kalau kamar itu bersebelahan dengan shahrukh khan, varun dhawan dan rohit shetty," ujar korban.

tak bisa berkutik, akhirnya korban hanya diam di kamar dan tidak bisa pergi ke mana-mana. sampai pada akhirnya morani kembali datang dan membawa minuman keras bersamanya

selain dikurung di dalam kamar, karim juga memaksa korban untuk meminum minuman keras. hal itu membuat korban tidak sadarkan diri dan ia pun menduga terjadi perkosaan pada malam itu
.
"morani datang ke kamar sekitar pukul 7 malam. dia membawa sebuah botol wine. aku bukan peminum, tapi dia memaksaku untuk minum. hal berikutnya yang aku tahu, aku bangun jam 4 pagi. aku bingung dan syok. fisik dan mental, aku syok.
name: Zona Bollywood

text:
#inktober day 13: guarded (swipe for close up)

this one is interesting. i’ve been worried about it since the beginning because it doesn’t inspire me in any way. at all. the only thing that comes to mind when i see this word is a big brick wall with something i want or need behind it. its an old wall, and there is a feeling of isolation. 
today is the first day that i have seen a distinct difference in the inktober posts from men and women. maybe it’s me and my perspective. women are posting about being guarded and not letting people in, about being constantly aware, about fear and needing to be guarded. men are posting more literal representations. of course it’s not everyone but it’s interesting.

i’ve enjoyed reading personal stories from everyone, and thank all the women who have shared, today. i don’t have a story for you today and i’m not going to write one for the sake of it. however i strongly believe that conversations and connections between people are going to change the world. 
this is my bit of wall. it's small but there is a lot behind it. but so many people around the world have bigger walls, physical or otherwise – i applaud those that are starting to tear them down and wish the best for those that haven’t found the strength yet. whether its letting people in or achieving things you never thought possible. you will get there.

all in all for a prompt i didn’t like it was a very interesting day. also i used a thicker pen today 05! sorry for the length!

text:
29 days in a row at the cinema and 262 on the year. today i saw indian / tamil-language thriller ratsasan (demon).
👹
ratsasan was my first ever indian film (tamil language / kollywood), and what an adventure it was. a 2-part, 2 1/2 hour movie about a frustrated film director who becomes a police officer and investigates murders of young girls using research he did for one of his scripts about serial killers, and i hardly felt the time pass.
⌚
what i appreciated about the film was the simplicity and straight forwardness of the directing, which harkens back to the old school style of filmmaking. imagine howard hawks or orson welles making a film like seven and you have an idea of what ratsasan is like.
🎬
also surprising was the subplot of the #metoo movement, where men who harassed women in various situations all received their come uppances. i'd read that india is beginning to experience a sea change as concerns the treatment of women, and while this film won't resolve all the issues, it at least is on the right side of them. 💜
as for the downside of the movie... it felt like too much time was spent stating the obvious and connecting the dots, but then again, in a nation of 1.3 billion people with 22 major languages, i imagine they have to keep the story somewhat low context to make sure everyone can follow along.
🤔
but this is a minor inconvenience, because the movie is loads of fun and the re-watch value is rather high. ratsasan may have been my first indian / tamil-language film, but i'll take pains to ensure it isn't my last.
👍🏼
out of a possible 10, i have 8 fs to give. strong #recommend. #film #cinema #review #movie #tamil #tamilcinema #indiancinema #ratsasan #amalapaul #ramkumar #vishnuvishal
🇮🇳
two interesting side notes. of all the films i've seen in paris, this was the first time i saw a warning not to smoke in the cinema and a reminder that both smoking and drinking liquor are bad for the health. secondly, i was shocked to see the subtitles were in english! most of the audience seemed to have an eastern connection, but if there were any frenchies there, i hope their english reading skills were up to par!
